NASSAU, Bahamas (AP) -- Hurricane Floyd pounded the Bahamas with   howling winds and blinding rain today, snapping palm trees in half,  downing power lines and churning up dangerous surf throughout the  vulnerable islands east of Florida.
NASSAU, Bahamas (AP) -- Hurricane Floyd strengthened to a very   dangerous Category 4 storm today with 155 mph wind, surprising  forecasters and charging toward the Bahamas on a path that also  threatened the Florida coast.
